Defendant Althea M Drummer in court with attorney Daryl A Kastenson.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Jelisa S. and Lisa C.  The Court imposed the following:

AS TO COUNT 01:
The Court imposed 9 months at the House of Correction, with credit for 2 days time served.  Court would allow good time and Huber privileges if working.  Court STAYED said sentence and placed defendant on probation for two (2) years.

AS TO COUNT 02:
The Court imposed 3 months at the House of Correction, with good time allowed and Huber if employed, consecutive to Count 1.  Court STAYED said sentence and placed defendant on probation for two (2) years, concurrent to Count 1.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION FOR COUNTS 1 AND 2:
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for her mental or physical needs; take as prescribed and only for as long as medically and reasonably necessary;
 - No alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - No contact in any way, shape, or form with Lisa C.;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Anger management;
 - Court imposed 60 days condition time at the House of Correction, to be used at the discretion of the agent for any violations;
 - Court ordered defendant to move from her current residence within 90 days of today's date (by 8/27/14);
 - Court ordered defendant to pay restitution to be determined at a later date; Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA surcharges for Counts 1 and 2, costs and disbursements.  Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Court ordered case adjourned for restitution hearing before Branch 20 on 6/16/14 at 8:30 a.m.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit form.
